 ','line_number':1,'multiline':True]['text':' By default, the primary should be connected to the secondary. Replicating a write should','line_number':38,'multiline':False]['text':' therefore succeed.','line_number':39,'multiline':False]['text':' We disconnect the primary from the secondary and verify that replicating a write fails.','line_number':42,'multiline':False]['text':' We restart the secondary and verify that replicating a write still fails.','line_number':46,'multiline':False]['text':' We restart the primary and verify that replicating a write still fails.','line_number':50,'multiline':False]['text':' Note that we specify 'primaryDB' to avoid having reconnect() send a message directly to the','line_number':53,'multiline':False]['text':' mongod process rather than going through the mongobridge process as well.','line_number':54,'multiline':False]['text':' We reconnect the primary to the secondary and verify that replicating a write succeeds.','line_number':58,'multiline':False]